Your email to the Governor's office was referred to me for response. As of right now, the projected start for construction of the final five-mile section of the I-485 loop remains 2015, because of major budget shortfalls faced by the N.C. Department of Transportation. Simply put, there isn't any money to do the work earlier unless new funding sources are found. To date, the Charlotte area has received nearly $1 billion in designated urban loop funding to construct the I-485 loop. That is more than any other city has received, but admittedly more is needed. Loop projects in Winston-Salem and Greensboro have also been delayed, and there is no funding planned for additional loop projects in Raleigh.

