Dear Ms. Jones:

Your email to the Governor's office has been forwarded to me for response.

Unfortunately, because of the poor economy and in particular, the financial hit the NC Department of Transportation has taken, tough decisions have had to be made. The NCDOT has a projected budget shortfall of more than $300 million for the 2008-2009 fiscal year. That has forced the Department to postpone about 75 percent of its projects, and to lay off its temporary and part-time employees across the state, with more cuts expected. In addition, no vacant permanent positions will be filled unless they are considered an essential position. In addition, no promotions or other salary adjustments may be made.

Facing an expected $2 billion deficit for this fiscal year, Governor Perdue has ordered all state agencies to cut their budgets by at least seven percent, and this week told members of the Council of State that agency personnel managers need to update their procedures for possible layoffs of full-time, permanent workers.

