Your email to the Governor's office was referred to me for response. Thank you for sharing your concerns about the US 501 project in Person County. As you mention, the widening of US 501 was identified as a need for Roxboro and Person County a number of years ago. Unfortunately, this type of project must compete for funding with many other projects across the state and it is nearly impossible for NCDOT to meet everyone's local priorities with the limited funding available. Due to this, the schedule for this project has had to move many times.

Project R-2241 is actually split into three sections. Section "A" (R-2241A) covers the highway from NC 49 in Roxboro to Halifax Road, while Section "B" (R-2241B) goes from Halifax Road to Old NC 501, and Section "C" (R-2241C) goes from Old NC 501 to just north of the Virginia State Line. 

