My name is Michael Hrabosky and am the owner of Total Lawn Care Solutions Inc., located outside of Greensboro, North Carolina.  Earlier today, I had the privilege of submitting proposals for contracts for Right of Way mowing and maintenance.  Specifically the were contract #'s : 
M-405 G-3 (41579.7.2 Loop), M-0405 G-2 (41549.7.1 Non-Loop) and, M-0405 G-1 (41549.7.1 Non-Loop).  

The bids process was promptly ended at 10:00 am,  as instructed by Kathy Smith.  The bids were opened and the documentation reviewed and forms completed by the Right of Way employees in the Greensboro office.  Kathy proceeded to announce the bid results, providing successful bid totals and the companies that received the recommendation for the contracts.  I notice that my figures were lower than the contractors awarded these bids. Before I had the chance to ask,  Kathy stated that, 2 of the 3 bids would have been awarded to another company, mine, however the proposal document was not the same as the one given out at the pre-bid meeting.  I waited until after the process was complete to speak with Kathy and her team.  Kathy explained that my form was not the exact form given out at the pre-bid meeting, my proposals were denied, however, would be sent to Raleigh for consideration, however was a high likelihood it would not be honored.  I would like to also point out, during the pre-bid meeting, no discussion took place on the first page format, as was discussed in great detail regarding the second signature page format and requirements.

The proposal document was not the original, because I transferred the information on the original form, which requires the numbers to be hand written, to an EXCEL spreadsheet, which with the correct formulas (matching the original document), would add my figures accurately.  In addition I had placed in the spreadsheet, formulas which would cross check my totals per line and indicate an error if the checks were not successful.  The items that were not included on my sheets were 1)  the page number and (2 the complete contract number (i.e. 41549.7.1 Non-Loop), the font was not the same as the original, however clear and readable.  Everything else was included, job quotes, totals (per mowing, per moth and per year), job locations, and more importantly the second pages containing my company name, my signature and corporate seal. I have attached the first page of the actual documents that I submitted.

As far as the dollar amounts and difference of my proposal vs. the awarded contractor, for Contract M-0405 G-1my bid was $6580.00 vs $8400.00, a difference of $1820.00, and for M-0405 G-3, my bid was $4970.00 vs. $6400.00, a difference of $1430.00.  The awarding of these contracts to myself  would save the State of North Carolina $3150.00.  Although just a small piece, unlike the numbers we are hearing from our government, trillions, billions and millions, I would be contributing toward the fiscal responsibility, we are so accustomed to hearing not only from our Governor, but also from our president, in some form or fashion.  In addition, the forms that still need to be hand written vs. automated are not only antiquated, but also inaccurate.

Please be clear, I am in no way faulting or blaming Kathy Smith or any members of their team for these comments, consideration and decision on my proposal contents.  They were just following instructions given to them.  My objection is that the same figures and totals that I submitted would be the same, regardless of which form I used.

I trust that you, my North Carolina Government Officials, will consider these circumstances when deciding if my proposals for these contracts are to be considered valid, and subsequently approved and awarded.  Thank you for your time and consideration.

